---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ToolHero from '../../components/ToolHero.astro';
import BridgeCTA from '../../components/BridgeCTA.astro';
import RelatedTools from '../../components/RelatedTools.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How to Keep ChatGPT Thinking Mode Always On | Auto Enable Reasoning"
  description="Tired of manually clicking the Think button? Learn how to auto-enable ChatGPT reasoning and keep extended thinking mode always on."
  canonicalPath="/guide/chatgpt-thinking-mode"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <meta name="keywords" content="chatgpt think mode always on, auto enable chatgpt reasoning mode, chatgpt reasoning mode extension chrome, chatgpt extended thinking automatic, never click think button chatgpt, how to keep chatgpt in think mode, chatgpt deep think automatically">

    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "HowTo",
      "name": "How to Auto-Enable ChatGPT Reasoning Mode",
      "description": "A quick guide on how to keep ChatGPT's extended thinking mode always on without manually clicking the button every time.",
      "step": [
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Install the Extension", "text": "Add the free ThinkMode+ extension to your Chrome or Edge browser." },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Open ChatGPT", "text": "Navigate to chatgpt.com. The ThinkMode+ persistent formatting bar will appear." },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Toggle Think Mode On", "text": "Click the 'Think Mode' toggle in the bar. From now on, every prompt you send will automatically trigger deep reasoning." }
      ]
    })} />

    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://thinkmodeplus.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Guides", "item": "https://thinkmodeplus.com/guide" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "ChatGPT Thinking Mode", "item": "https://thinkmodeplus.com/guide/chatgpt-thinking-mode" }
      ]
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <div class="tool-page">
    <ToolHero 
      title="How to Keep ChatGPT Thinking Mode Always On"
      subtitle="Stop manually clicking the 'Think' button for every prompt. Learn how to auto-enable reasoning mode so ChatGPT defaults to deep, logical answers every time."
      breadcrumbToolName="Thinking Mode Guide"
      toolPath="/guide/chatgpt-thinking-mode"
    />

    <article class="guide-content">
      <div class="guide-intro">
        <p>If you're using ChatGPT for coding, writing, or deep research, you already know that <strong>Reasoning Mode</strong> (or "Extended Thinking") drastically improves the quality of the output.</p>
        <p>The problem? <strong>OpenAI forces you to manually click the "Think" button before every single complex prompt.</strong> If you forget to click it, you get a shallow, hallucinated answer, and you have to regenerate the entire response.</p>
        <p>Here is the exact 30-second workaround to make ChatGPT default to deep thinking automatically.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="solution-box">
        <h2>The Solution: ThinkMode+</h2>
        <p>ThinkMode+ is a lightweight browser extension that injects a persistent "Precision Bar" directly into the ChatGPT interface. Among other formatting tools, it includes a <strong>permanent Think toggle.</strong></p>
        
        <div class="steps-grid">
          <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-num">1</div>
            <h3>Install the Extension</h3>
            <p>Add ThinkMode+ to Chrome or Edge. It's completely free and requires no signup.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-num">2</div>
            <h3>Flip the Switch</h3>
            <p>Open ChatGPT and click the new 🧠 Think toggle injected above your chatbox.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-num">3</div>
            <h3>Never Click it Again</h3>
            <p>That's it. Every prompt you send will now automatically trigger deep reasoning mode.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="guide-faq">
        <h2>Why does this matter?</h2>
        <p>When you force the AI into reasoning mode, it performs a hidden "Chain of Thought" (CoT) process before it starts typing. It breaks down your prompt, analyzes edge cases, and double-checks its own logic. By making this automatic, you eliminate the cognitive load of having to constantly babysit the AI's settings.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <BridgeCTA 
      heading="Ready to upgrade your ChatGPT workflow?"
      subtext="Install ThinkMode+ now. Auto-enable reasoning mode, generate Markdown tables with one click, and inject expert personas directly into your chatbox."
      link="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/thinkmode+/gdaonnlalhpjhddfpbfdkhjhinbideni"
      btnText="Install ThinkMode+ Free"
    />

    <RelatedTools />
  </div>

  <style>
    .tool-page { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 24px 80px; }

    .guide-content { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 64px; }
    
    .guide-intro p { margin-bottom: 24px; color: var(--text-dim); }
    .guide-intro strong { color: var(--text); }
    
    .solution-box { background: var(--bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 16px; padding: 32px; margin: 40px 0; }
    .solution-box h2 { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--accent-pink); }
    .solution-box p { color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 32px; }

    .steps-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 24px; }
    @media (max-width: 768px) { .steps-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
    
    .step-card { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border-hi); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; position: relative; }
    .step-num { position: absolute; top: -12px; left: -12px; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: var(--accent); color: #fff; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px; box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(186, 58, 184, 0.3); }
    .step-card h3 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin: 8px 0; }
    .step-card p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-dim); margin: 0; }

    .guide-faq h2 { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 16px; }
    .guide-faq p { color: var(--text-dim); }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
